r, teacher, artist and \u201cculture-carrier\u201d', <a href=\"/wiki/Eye_(magazine)\" title=\"Eye (magazine)\">Eye (magazine)</a>, Autumn 1993, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/letters-in-the-city\">http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/letters-in-the-city</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">'New Scotland Yard's iconic revolving sign has moved', <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://content.met.police.uk/News/New-Scotland-Yards-iconic-revolving-sign-has-moved/1400009560249/1257246741786\">http://content.met.police.uk/News/New-Scotland-Yards-iconic-revolving-sign-has-moved/1400009560249/1257246741786</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.optimism-modernity.org.uk/events/wright/see/reminiscences/index.html/\">Reminiscences and obituaries</a> Retrieved on 27 Mar 2018</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Edward_Wright_(artist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Paul Stiff and Petra Cerne Oven, 'Edward Wright \u2013 unrecognised pioneer of British graphic design', <i><a href=\"/wiki/Baseline_(magazine)\" title=\"Baseline (magazine)\">Baseline</a></i> 52, edited by Hans Dieter Reichert, Bradbourne Publishing, 2007\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Edward_Wright_(artist)&amp;action=edit&amp;secti